The band played all of the DFW rock clubs including Savvy's, On The Rocks, Dallas City Limits and The Basement. They also played the southwestern United States club circuit from El Paso to Houston to Kansas City and all points in between.

In late 1988 Chastity released their self titled debut. Several tracks, including the radio ready "Can't Get Over You," were featured on Q102's Texas Tapes.

Chastity played their last show in El Paso, Texas in the summer of 1990. The band was resurrected in 2012 when they were invited to play the On The Rocks Reunion show at LaGrange in Dallas on August 17. 

The band lost a member of its brotherhood four years ago when original bassist Gerry Cummings passed away from cancer. Gerry was a great friend and an integral part of Chastity. He is loved and missed every day.

Thanks to the overwhelming reception from fans and friends at the August show in Dallas, the band will begin writing new material and schedule a few shows in 2013! 

A heartfelt "thank you" to all of you who came to the On The Rocks Reunion to support us! Over the last 22 years we never thought we would ever play together again, much less schedule future club dates. YOU made this possible! Thank you! We love ya!
